    <section id="faq" data-section-key="faq">
      <div class="wrap">
        <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <details><summary>What does it cost?</summary><p>Ongoing care starts at €149/month, for example one server and up to five workstations. We agree the right scope clearly up front. For one-off, clearly scoped projects you get a fixed-price offer with scope, price and process after the initial consultation. For unclear or grown environments we start with an IT infrastructure analysis at a price agreed in advance, before an implementation offer is made. Larger software undertakings are split into traceable phases where needed.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Am I locked into a contract?</summary><p>Pure projects are one-off engagements with a clearly agreed scope. Ongoing care can be cancelled. I want to convince through reliable work, not through unnecessarily long contract terms.</p></details>
        <details><summary>What happens in an outage or data loss?</summary><p>For acute issues you reach me directly by phone and I deal with it as a priority. For maintenance clients a fixed response time can be agreed to match the package. As a precaution, tested backups are in place: we verify restores <em>before</em> the emergency and document how they work.</p></details>
        <details><summary>You work alone, what happens if you're unavailable?</summary><p>Fair question. I document systems and access so they're ready to hand over and someone else can take over in an emergency, instead of hoarding knowledge in my head. On top of that come the tested, off-site backups with verified recovery. So your operation doesn't depend on my presence, and you aren't made artificially dependent.</p></details>
        <details><summary>How do you handle data protection and GDPR?</summary><p>A data processing agreement (DPA) is part of every engagement. Data stays on systems in Germany, backups are encrypted, access rights are clearly defined. I work aligned with the German BSI baseline-protection methodology, which is a way of working, not a certification.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do you see our data when maintaining our systems?</summary><p>To maintain your IT I need access to systems, not to your content. I work on configuration, structure and scripts. Your actual data (database contents, documents, emails) stays on your systems. If a specific task genuinely requires real data, it only happens by arrangement, documented, and under the data processing agreement.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Will I understand what's being done?</summary><p>Yes, that's part of the job. No jargon, everything documented in writing and explained so you can pass it on to your team.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do you use AI for development?</summary><p>Yes, as a tool for routine work. Architecture, security, review and responsibility stay with me. Your confidential content is not simply fed into public AI services.</p></details>
      </div>
    </section>

